Sentencas: Electrical conductivity of Sr2-xVMoO6-y (x = 0.0, 0.1, 0.2) double perovskites has been investigated in a reducing atmosphere at temperatures up to 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity of Sr2-xVMoO6-y (x=0.0, 0.1, 0.2) double perovskites

Sentencas: This material has a key application in solid oxide fuel cell anodes as a mixed ion and electron conductor.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity of Sr2-xVMoO6-y (x=0.0, 0.1, 0.2) double perovskites

Sentencas: A solid state synthesis technique was used to fabricate materials and crystal structure was verified through x-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity of Sr2-xVMoO6-y (x=0.0, 0.1, 0.2) double perovskites

Sentencas: Subsequent to conventional sintering in a reducing environment, elemental valence states were indentified through x-ray photoemission spectroscopy on the double perovskite material before and after annealing in a hydrogen environment.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity of Sr2-xVMoO6-y (x=0.0, 0.1, 0.2) double perovskites

Sentencas: Samples exhibited metallic like conduction with electrical conductivities of 1250 S/cm (Sr2VMoO6-y'), 2530 S/cm (Sr1.8VMoO6-y ''), and 3610 S/cm (Sr1.9VMoO6-y''') at 800 degrees C in 5% H-2/95% N-2, with a substantial increase in conductivity upon cooling to room temperature.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity of Sr2-xVMoO6-y (x=0.0, 0.1, 0.2) double perovskites

Sentencas: Room temperature electrical conductivity values for Sr1.9VMoO6-y''' make it a candidate as the highest electrically conductive oxide known.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity of Sr2-xVMoO6-y (x=0.0, 0.1, 0.2) double perovskites

Sentencas: Highly insulating secondary surface phases, Sr3V2O8, and SrMoO4, begin to reduce at 400 degrees C in a hydrogen environment, as confirmed by X-ray photoemission and thermal gravimetric analysis.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity of Sr2-xVMoO6-y (x=0.0, 0.1, 0.2) double perovskites

Sentencas: This reduction, from V5+ and Mo6+ to lower valence states, leads to a large increase in sample electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Electrical conductivity of Sr2-xVMoO6-y (x=0.0, 0.1, 0.2) double perovskites
